Aim

To perform logical operations using 8051.

Theory
Logical instructions operate on bits
AND masks bits
OR sets bits
XOR toggles bits
CPL complements data
RL and RR rotate bits
Used in control systems
Simulator Used

EdSim51

Code
ORG 0000H

; AND
MOV A, #0F5H
MOV R0, #0A3H
ANL A, R0

; OR
MOV A, #55H
MOV R1, #0AAH
ORL A, R1

; XOR
MOV A, #5AH
MOV R2, #3CH
XRL A, R2

; CPL
MOV A, #96H
CPL A

SJMP $
END
Observation
AND, OR, XOR executed correctly
CPL complemented bits
Results verified in A
Conclusion

Thus, logical operations were successfully verified.
